@@ -0,0 +1,74 @@
+# Why CVE-2026-39865 Is Not Applicable to axios@1.7.9
+
+This document confirms that **CVE-2026-39865** does **not affect** axios@1.7.9, and explains why no patch or backport is required for this version.
+
+---
+
+## Overview
+
+CVE-2026-39865 describes a state-corruption denial-of-service vulnerability in the HTTP/2 session cleanup logic (`Http2Sessions.getSession()`) inside `lib/adapters/http.js`. A malicious HTTP/2 server can crash the Node.js client process by triggering concurrent session closures via GOAWAY frames that exploit a broken loop in `Http2Sessions.removeSession()`.
+
+---
+
+## CVE Details
+
+- **CVE ID**: CVE-2026-39865
+- **GHSA**: GHSA-qj83-cq47-w5f8
+- **CVSS Score**: 5.9
+- **Severity**: MEDIUM
+- **CWE**: CWE-400 (Uncontrolled Resource Consumption), CWE-662 (Improper Synchronization)
+- **Published**: 2026-04-07
+- **Fix Version**: axios 1.13.2
+
+---
+
+## Why This Does Not Affect axios@1.7.9
+
+The vulnerable `Http2Sessions` class and all HTTP/2 session management code were introduced in **PR #7150** (`feat(http): add HTTP2 support`), which was merged on **2025-10-19** and first shipped as **axios@1.13.0**.
+
+axios@1.7.9 predates this feature by more than five minor versions. The following symbols referenced by the CVE are **entirely absent** from the v1.7.9 codebase:
+
+| Symbol | Status in v1.7.9 |
+|--------|------------------|
+| `Http2Sessions` class | Does NOT exist |
+| `getSession()` method | Does NOT exist |
+| `removeSession()` callback | Does NOT exist |
+| HTTP/2 adapter code | Does NOT exist |
+
+Because the vulnerable code path simply does not exist in axios@1.7.9, the vulnerability cannot be triggered on this version. No patch or backport is applicable or necessary.
+
+---
+
+## Affected Version Range
+
+- **Vulnerable range**: axios >= 1.13.0 and < 1.13.2
+- **Not affected**: axios < 1.13.0 (including v1.7.9)
+- **Fixed version**: axios 1.13.2
+
+---
+
+## Validation Findings
+
+| Check | Result |
+|-------|--------|
+| CVE is active and valid | Yes |
+| `Http2Sessions` class exists in v1.7.9 | **No** |
+| HTTP/2 adapter code exists in v1.7.9 | **No** |
+| Vulnerable code path reachable in v1.7.9 | **No** |
+| Patch applicable to v1.7.9 | **No** |
+
+---
+
+## References
+
+- [NVD — CVE-2026-39865](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-39865)
+- [GitHub Advisory GHSA-qj83-cq47-w5f8](https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-qj83-cq47-w5f8)
+- [axios PR #7150 — feat(http): add HTTP2 support (merged 2025-10-19)](https://github.com/axios/axios/pull/7150)
+- [axios PR #7202 — Upstream Fix (v1.13.2)](https://github.com/axios/axios/pull/7202)
+
